cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on cross-lingual transfer of neural models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural architectures and weak supervision, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions sentiment analysis, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), making these categories less likely but still possible.
